>Jesse: AGGIIUU -GGIIUU +0 150
#note keep A because only two unseen. but actually, Q likes playing GIGUE and playing through - the pool is really consonant-heavy, so AIU will tend to fill in with consonants more than you'd think, and it blocks a ton of bingos that could put him up (Tarin is 23% to bingo after exchange, 15% after GIGUE)
>Tarin: BELMOPR 4C PROBL.M +26 196
>Jesse: AEFIJNR F2 JA. +28 178
#note I'm losing, and FAIRER at 5E doesn't seem to leave any particularly good J plays. I'll take JAB even though it sims 2-3 points beneath.
>Tarin: DEERUWY 6F WE.RY +27 223
#note WOW he has UPDREW/WANTHILL!! I would've lost my mind if he played that.
>Jesse: EEFINRV 5J FIVE +28 206
>Tarin: DEKLNRU N5 RUNKLED +77 300
#note awesome find!!! he also has KNURLED for 12 more in the same spot, but still a courageous play from the 17 year-old. for context, Kenji chickened out of this word at the peak of his abilities at a mid-2000s Nationals.
>Jesse: EEIMNOR L5 .OMERINE +78 284
#note the question - do I need to go for OVERMINE here for 4 more points? He has about a 81% chance of having one of the 3 Ds, one of the Ss or the blank (his rack is random), and I liked my chances better of catching him with normal play. If I were down more points I'd have to think about setting the hook up.
>Tarin: ?AGIOTT O8 AIT +31 331
>Jesse: CDDEGUX M12 DUX +25 309
#note I didn't love this, but nothing is very happy inducing. DUG at M12 sets up the X at K12, but not for enough points to be useful, and Tarin is very likely to have at least one of the 3 Ss and cash it if he needs to. Cashing EX for 38 leaves a miserable keep. CUDDIE at 7A is at least a clever try to go for a XU/XI play, although it will likely give Tarin free points. In hindsight I would probably play DUG and hope to draw into COXES at O1 or similar.
>Tarin: ?DEGOTU N13 GUT +29 360
>Jesse: CDEEGST O1 CEDES +39 348
